    "title_html": "What you're <em>looking</em> at.",
    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "A statement color. Max Def Burnt Sienna works when the rest of the elevation already commits to warm-tone stucco, terracotta, or stone. The granule blend is layered enough that the color reads as architectural rather than novelty.",
      "The shingle profile holds enough shadow line that the warm tones deepen at sunset rather than washing out. Florida midday sun flatters this color especially well.",
      "A natural choice if your elevation has warm stucco, terracotta, or natural-stone accents. Best avoided on cool modern builds."
    ],
